{"guideId":"f2bf6964-b603-4126-885b-fe18611f4225","chunks":[{"content":"Photosynthesis is the process by which plants, algae, and some bacteria convert light energy into chemical energy. Using sunlight, carbon dioxide, and water, they produce glucose and oxygen. This process is fundamental to life on Earth as it is the primary source of organic material and oxygen in the atmosphere. The chemical equation is 6CO2 + 6H2O + light energy -> C6H12O6 + 6O2. It takes place in the chloroplasts, specifically within the thylakoid membranes (light reactions) and the stroma (Calvin cycle).","embedding":[-0.07671093195676804,0.06910808384418488,-0.11670317500829697,0.07615131884813309,0.037493813782930374,0.010516539216041565,0.038779497146606445,0.01133022177964449,0.0700865313410759,0.07232660800218582,0.02069094218313694,-0.05475757643580437,-0.043144140392541885,-0.04035573825240135,0.015746185556054115,0.057323701679706573,-0.07760999351739883,0.014785864390432835,-0.050884559750556946,-0.034404393285512924,0.09011391550302505,-0.0016272831708192825,-0.048245105892419815,-0.01971299573779106,0.025667186826467514,-0.0034930617548525333,-0.07477865368127823,-0.020799670368433,0.0030830486211925745,0.00026617548428475857,0.007823614403605461,0.05594194307923317,0.036136362701654434,-0.03261829912662506,0.06370185315608978,0.13841865956783295,0.006963600870221853,-0.14757058024406433,0.000784710980951786,0.034754008054733276,-0.07411050796508789,-0.056351516395807266,-0.003048528451472521,0.03180045634508133,-0.042456161230802536,-0.005377813708037138,0.03733948618173599,0.02153143845498562,-0.0485474094748497,-0.06992980092763901,-0.0022575464099645615,-0.0007715789834037423,-0.11749239265918732,-0.012561958283185959,0.056934744119644165,0.008888546377420425,0.012607638724148273,-0.001743623986840248,0.06771622598171234,-0.06406504660844803,0.05986018106341362,-0.05483314394950867,-0.00588646437972784,0.006196433678269386,0.047850724309682846,-0.026840653270483017,0.0258615594